snippet: The rebels said Thursday that they had ambushed a military patrol, killing 10 soldiers, and shot down a government warplane.
abstract: Sudan People's Liberation Movement-North says it ambushed military patrol, killing 10 soldiers, and shot down government warplane.
lead_paragraph: The rebels said Thursday that they had ambushed a military patrol, killing 10 soldiers, and shot down a government warplane.

headline.main: Sudan: Rebels Claim They Shot Down Military Plane
